age does not demonstrate motion artifact, as this is a separate acquisition.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2017170032&amp;id=fig11c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">1.</div><div id="r1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Roth RG, Maidment AD, Weinstein SP, Roth SO, Conant EF. Digital breast tomosynthesis: lessons learned from early clinical implementation. <em>RadioGraphics</em> 2014;34(4):E89–E102.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.344130087">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25019451/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Digital+breast+tomosynthesis%3A+lessons+learned+from+early+clinical+implementation&amp;author=RG+Roth&amp;author=AD+Maidment&amp;author=SP+Weinstein&amp;author=SO+Roth&amp;author=EF+Conant&amp;publication_year=2014&amp;journal=RadioGraphics&amp;pages=E89-E102&amp;doi=10.1148%2Frg.344130087&amp;pmid=25019451">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">2.</div><div id="r2" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Peppard HR, Nicholson BE, Rochman CM, Merchant JK, Mayo RC 3rd, Harvey JA. Digital breast tomosynthesis in the diagnostic setting: indications and clinical applications. <em>RadioGraphics</em> 2015;35(4):975–990.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.2015140204">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26024062/">PubMed</a></